<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>7. Create metrics with Count Connector on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector/7-sum-count/</link><description>Recent content in 7. Create metrics with Count Connector on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector/7-sum-count/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>7.1 Testing the Count Connector</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector/7-sum-count/7-1-count-test/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector/7-sum-count/7-1-count-test/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
